text.section:
The freshwater fishing guide license is not valid in tidal waters except for the following designated areas:
In the upper Chesapeake Bay upstream of a line from Sandy Point to Turkey Point;
In the Elk River upstream of a line from Turkey Point to the State launching ramp at Pearce Creek;
In the Pond Creek upstream of a line connecting the two unnamed points at the entrance to the creek;
In the Sassafras River upstream of a line from Grove Point to Howell Point;
In the Still Pond Creek upstream of a line from Meeks Point to Rocky Point;
In the Worton Creek upstream of a line from the point at Copeland to Handys Point;
In the Fairlee Creek upstream of a line across the entrance of the creek;
In the Chester River upstream of a line from Spaniard Point to Nichols Point;
In the Corsica River, a tributary of the Chester River, upstream of a line from Spaniard Point to Holton Point;
In the Langford Creek, a tributary of the Chester River, upstream of a line from Nichols Point to Grays Inn Point;
In the Grays Inn Creek, a tributary of the Chester River upstream from Grays Inn Point to Little Gum Point;
In the Choptank River upstream of the Dover Bridge on Route 331;
In the Blackwater River upstream of a line from the lower point of Snake Island to the southernmost point on the opposite shore;
In the Transquaking River upstream of a line from Alabaster Point running magnetic north to the opposite shore;
In the Nanticoke River upstream of a line from Long Point to Runaway Point;
In the Wicomico River upstream of the Whitehaven ferry crossing;
In the Pocomoke River upstream of the landing at Rehobeth;
In the Maryland tributaries of the Potomac River above the Route 301 bridge; and
In the Wicomico River, a tributary of the Potomac River, upstream of a line from Mills Point in a westerly direction to the northernmost point at the entrance to Dolly Boarmans Creek;
In the Patuxent River upstream of the overhead power lines north of Gods Grace Point;
In the Swanson Creek, a tributary of the Patuxent River, upstream of a line from Teague Point to Chalk Point;
In the Patapsco River upstream of the Hanover Street crossing parallel to the Potee Street crossing;
In the Back River upstream of a line from Cuckhold Point to Rocky Point;
In the Middle River upstream of a line from Booby Point to Bowley Bar Point;
In the Seneca Creek upstream of a line from Bowley Bar Point to Lowen Point;
In the Gunpowder River upstream of a line from Weir Point to Rickett Point; and
In the Bush River upstream of a line from Abbey Point to Sandy Point.

The Department shall adopt regulations necessary to implement this section including regulations that:
Prohibit a person from furnishing any service as a fishing guide that requires operating a boat or vessel as part of that service without complying with appropriate federal regulations governing the operation of a vessel carrying passengers for hire;
Limit to 150 the number of freshwater fishing guide licenses that will be issued annually that allow a person to operate in nontidal freshwater and tidal water areas designated in subsection (f) of this section;
Allocate not more than 20% to nonresidents of the 150 freshwater fishing guide licenses that allow a person to operate in nontidal freshwater and tidal areas designated in subsection (f) of this section; and
Establish provisions for maintaining a waiting list for applicants in excess of the maximum number of fishing guide licenses that allow a person to operate in nontidal freshwater and tidal areas designated in subsection (f) of this section.
